President Biden spoke with President Putin of Russia to discuss various regional and global issues. They expressed their intention to engage in a strategic stability dialogue on arms control and emerging security matters, building upon the extension of the New START Treaty. President Biden emphasized that the United States will defend its national interests firmly against actions by Russia, such as cyber intrusions and election interference. He also reiterated the United States' commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, expressing concerns about the Russian military build-up in occupied Crimea and on Ukraine's borders, and calling for de-escalation. President Biden aims to establish a stable and predictable relationship with Russia, aligned with U.S. interests, and proposed a summit in a third country in the coming months to address a wide range of issues.